    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA uses a two-column dashboard layout. A sticky left-hand navigation panel provides constant access to key sections, while the right-hand content area allows for focused exploration. This non-linear structure enables recruiters to quickly access the information most relevant to them, such as skills or projects. The user flow is designed to guide from a high-level overview to detailed deep-dives, creating a more engaging narrative of the candidate's career progression than a traditional linear resume. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Career Timeline: Report Info -> Job History Dates. Goal -> Show progression. Viz -> Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction -> Hover for details. Justification -> Visually summarizes career length and stages instantly.
        - Skills Assessment: Report Info -> Technical Skills List. Goal -> Compare proficiency. Viz -> Grouped Horizontal Bar Charts (Chart.js). Interaction -> Hover for proficiency level. Justification -> More impactful and easier to compare skill strengths than a static list.
        - Project Showcase: Report Info -> Key Projects List. Goal -> Organize and detail project experience. Viz -> Interactive HTML/CSS cards. Interaction -> Click to expand/reveal details. Justification -> Turns a simple list into an engaging portfolio highlight.
        - Navigation: Report Info -> Resume Sections. Goal -> Guide user. Viz -> Highlighted links. Interaction -> Click to scroll and highlight. Justification -> Standard, effective UX for SPAs.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
